# Zephyria Codebase Standardization & Full Integration

This plan resolves all subsystem disconnections, eliminates TODOs, and creates a unified execution flow where every component—DAG mempool, consensus, storage, P2P, VM, SDK, and RPC—is fully aware of and integrated with every other component, targeting 1M TPS on mid-tier consumer hardware.

## Codebase Gap Analysis Summary

| Issue | Severity | Location |
|:---|:---|:---|
| Miner uses legacy `TxPool` instead of DAG mempool | **Critical** | `src/node/miner.zig:310` |
| `BlockProducer` has DAG support but is not used by Miner | **Critical** | [src/core/block_producer.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/core/block_producer.zig) |
| DAG executor has no VM callback wired | **Critical** | `src/core/dag_executor.zig:139` |
| VM Bridge uses global mutable `callback_bridge` | **High** | `src/vm_bridge.zig:118` |
| TurboExecutor instantiated in [main.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/main.zig) but not driving DAG | **High** | `src/main.zig:464` |
| P2P broadcasts raw blocks instead of Turbine shreds | **High** | `src/node/miner.zig:202-208` |
| Gulf Stream not connected to DAG mempool | **High** | [src/p2p/gulf_stream.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/gulf_stream.zig) |
| RPC references legacy `TxPool` and `Executor` | **Medium** | `src/rpc/methods.zig:13-14` |
| Consensus pipeline finalization doesn't drive commit | **Medium** | [src/consensus/pipeline.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/consensus/pipeline.zig) |
| 11 TODOs across storage, P2P, and crypto | **Medium** | Various |

