## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Core Execution Pipeline — DAG-Native Miner

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is the most critical change. Currently the Miner pulls TXs from the legacy `TxPool` and executes via `Executor.apply_block()`. The entire DAG pipeline (mempool → scheduler → executor) exists but is disconnected. This change wires the Miner through `BlockProducer` which already has DAG support.

#### [MODIFY] [miner.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/node/miner.zig)

- Replace `tx_pool: *tx_pool_mod.TxPool` + `executor: *executor_mod.Executor` with `block_producer: *block_producer_mod.BlockProducer`
- Rewrite `produce_block()` to delegate to `BlockProducer.produce()` (which already supports DAG + legacy fallback)
- Keep thread partitioning and woven root as post-processing on top of `BlockProducer.BuildResult`
- Wire block rewards into `BlockProducer` result
- Remove direct `tx_pool.get_transactions()` and `tx_pool.remove_executed()` calls — `BlockProducer` handles pool lifecycle
- Keep all epoch, pipeline, staking, and P2P integration logic intact

#### [MODIFY] [block_producer.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/core/block_producer.zig)

- Add VM callback field and propagation to DAG executor
- Add block rewards integration into both DAG and legacy paths
- Add security sanitizer check before DAG admission
- Add Verkle trie commit + root computation in post-execution

#### [MODIFY] [dag_executor.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/core/dag_executor.zig)

- Add `VMCallback` field (matching `core.executor.VMCallback` interface)
- Wire VM callback into per-lane execution for contract calls
- Integrate `security.GasMeter` per-TX for gas accounting
- Add `security.ReentrancyGuard` per-lane for call depth tracking
- Implement async state root: compute deltas synchronously, return immediately, hash asynchronously

#### [MODIFY] [dag_mempool.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/core/dag_mempool.zig)

- Wire `security.TxSanitizer` at admission (`submit()`) before lane insertion
- Wire `security.TxBloomFilter` for O(1) duplicate detection at admission
- Wire `security.RateLimiter` at admission (per-sender rate gating)
- Expose `getMetrics()` for RPC consumption

---

### Phase 2: VM Bridge — Thread-Safe & DAG-Integrated

#### [MODIFY] [vm_bridge.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/vm_bridge.zig)

- Remove global `var callback_bridge: *VMBridge` — this is inherently thread-unsafe and will corrupt state during parallel DAG lane execution
- Pass `VMBridge` pointer through the callback context (`ctx: *anyopaque`) which is already available in the `VMCallback` interface
- Add execution timeout via `security.ExecutionTimer` per contract call
- Add reentrancy tracking per call chain
- Pool `StateBridge` instances for zero-allocation execution (pre-allocate per-thread)

#### [MODIFY] [state_bridge.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/vm/riscv/state_bridge.zig)

- Add write_key enforcement: verify that any `SSTORE`/`SLOAD` syscall targets only keys declared in the TX's `DAGVertex.write_keys`
- This enforces the mathematical isolation guarantee at the VM level as defense-in-depth

---

### Phase 3: Storage — Resolving TODOs & Performance

#### [MODIFY] [lsm/db.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/storage/lsm/db.zig)

- Implement SSTable flush at line 77: when memtable exceeds threshold, flush to SSTable file using existing `SSTableWriter`

#### [MODIFY] [lsm/io.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/storage/lsm/io.zig)

- Implement `io_uring` engine at line 180 for Linux, with runtime detection and fallback to thread-pool I/O on macOS/other platforms

#### [MODIFY] [zephyrdb/mod.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/storage/zephyrdb/mod.zig)

- Fix arena slice return at line 291 to return proper slice from arena memory
- Add striped locks to `AccountTable` for concurrent delta merge (partition lock by address prefix, matching DAG shard assignment)

#### [MODIFY] [zephyrdb/checkpoint.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/storage/zephyrdb/checkpoint.zig)

- Implement double-buffered checkpoint: Arena A serialized to disk by background thread while executor mutates Arena B

#### [MODIFY] [epoch/signature_aggregator.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/storage/epoch/signature_aggregator.zig)

- Optimize memory allocation at line 149: pre-allocate aggregation buffer, reuse across epochs

