### Phase 4: Consensus ↔ Execution Flow

#### [MODIFY] [zelius.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/consensus/zelius.zig)

- Wire `verify_vote_signature()` to actually verify BLS signature (currently returns `true` unconditionally at line 367)
- Add equivocation evidence broadcast: when `recordProposal()` detects double-signing, create a P2P `SlashEvent` message for network-wide propagation
- Add exponential backoff on view change timeout to prevent packet storms during network partitions

#### [MODIFY] [pipeline.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/consensus/pipeline.zig)

- Connect `finalize()` to actual commit: when proposal finalizes, trigger state persistence and irreversibility marker in ZephyrDB
- Pause proposals momentarily during epoch transition to allow signature weight recalculation

#### [MODIFY] [staking.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/consensus/staking.zig)

- Wire validator set rotation output into `ZeliusEngine.rotateEpoch()`'s input: provide updated `active_validators` slice

---

### Phase 5: P2P ↔ All Subsystems

#### [MODIFY] [p2p/server.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/server.zig)

- Activate `TurbineEngine` as primary block propagation path: shred blocks via Reed-Solomon before broadcast
- Route inbound `SlashEvent` messages to consensus engine for validator tombstoning
- Wire received TXs through DAG mempool admission (not legacy pool)

#### [MODIFY] [p2p/gulf_stream.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/gulf_stream.zig)

- Connect Gulf Stream TX forwarding to DAG mempool: pre-forward TXs to predicted next leader's DAG for parallel admission

#### [MODIFY] [p2p/quic/transport/stream.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/quic/transport/stream.zig)

- Implement QUIC stream flush (TODO at line 60)

---

### Phase 6: RPC Integration

#### [MODIFY] [rpc/methods.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/rpc/methods.zig)

- Add optional `dag_pool: ?*dag_mempool.DAGMempool` reference to `RpcHandler`
- Update `eth_sendRawTransaction` to route through DAG mempool admission (with sanitizer)
- Update `eth_getTransactionCount` to check DAG mempool pending nonce
- Add Zephyria-specific RPC methods:
  - `zeph_getDAGMetrics`: shard stats, lane counts, vertex counts
  - `zeph_getThreadInfo`: consensus tier, thread count, epoch info
  - `zeph_getBlockProducerStats`: DAG execution timing, parallel lane counts

#### [MODIFY] [rpc/http_server.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/rpc/http_server.zig)

- Wire DAG mempool reference into RPC handler initialization

---

### Phase 7: main.zig — Unified Wiring

#### [MODIFY] [main.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/main.zig)

- Create `BlockProducer` with DAG pipeline (DAG mempool + DAG scheduler + DAG executor)
- Wire VM bridge into DAG executor (not just legacy executor)
- Wire security module (rate limiter, sanitizer, bloom filter) into DAG mempool
- Create DAG mempool and pass it to both BlockProducer and RPC
- Pass `BlockProducer` to Miner instead of legacy pool+executor
- Remove TurboExecutor (its fast-path optimization is integrated into DAG executor)
- Wire Turbine into P2P server as primary propagation
- Wire gulf_stream into P2P with DAG mempool reference

---

### Phase 8: build.zig — Module Dependencies

#### [MODIFY] [build.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/build.zig)

- Add `storage` import to `consensus_mod` (for epoch rotation persistence)
- Add `vm_bridge` import to `core_mod` (for DAG executor VM callback)
- Add `p2p` import to `consensus_mod` (for equivocation gossip)
- Update test targets for new integration points

